[Karnataka suffers from chronic enzootic anthrax. Taking just the past 6 years, 2007-2012, there were 16 livestock outbreaks in 2007; 10 outbreaks in 2008 but some 457 sheep and goats were affected; 18 outbreaks in 2009 with 1155 sheep and goats affected and buffaloes; 17 outbreaks in 2010, including buffaloes; 9 outbreaks in 2011, including cattle and sheep and goats; and 4 in 2012, but 101 small ruminants affected in just 2 outbreaks. There were no human cases reported during that period.

For maps of India showing Karnataka and Tamil Nadu states, see http://healthmap.org/r/2kP3 and http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/india_pol01.jpg. A map showing the location of the Karnataka wildlife reserves mentioned in the article can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/wildlife/wildlife-karnataka.htm. - Mod.MHJ]
